cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SY 

This paper discusses the computation of mutual information in large sets of data, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper also discusses the Triple-Helix model, which is a framework for university-industry-government relations and can be considered a form of social informatics (cs.SI). The use of an open-source routine for computation suggests a focus on computational methods (cs.CY), and the discussion of synergy in university-industry-government relations suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
